8 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
9 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
10 Article – Education
11 4–147.
12 (A) (1) IN THIS SECTION THE FOLLOWING WORDS HAVE THE MEANINGS
13 INDICATED.
14 (2) “ASSIGNING FEES” MEANS THE FEES CHARGED BY AN ASSIGNOR.
15 (3) “ASSIGNOR” MEANS AN OFFICIATING ASSOCIATION OR
16 ORGANIZATION OR AN INDEPENDENT CONTRACTOR THAT:
17 (I) IS REGISTERED AND IN GOOD STANDING WITH THE STATE
18 DEPARTMENT OF ASSESSMENTS AND TAXATION; AND
19 (II) PROVIDES, ASSIGNS, AND SCHEDULES THE OFFICIALS THAT
20 PROVIDE THE HIGH SCHOOL SPORTS OFFICIATING SERVICES FOR A HIGH SCHOOL
21 SPORTING EVENT.
22 (2) “HIGH SCHOOL SPORTS OFFICIAL” MEANS AN OFFICIAL, AN
23 UMPIRE, A REFEREE, OR A JUDGE WHO PRESIDES OVER A SPORTING EVENT TO
24 GUARANTEE THAT THE RULES OF THE EVENT ARE ENFORCED.
25 (3) “HIGH SCHOOL SPORTS OFFICIATING ROLE” MEANS AN
26 OFFICIATING ASSIGNMENT FOR A HIGH SCHOOL SPORTS OFFICIAL THAT REQUIRES
27 PERFORMANCE OF A DEFINED SET OF HIGH SCHOOL SPORTS OFFICIATING SERVICES.
28 (4) “HIGH SCHOOL SPORTS OFFICIATING SERVICES” MEANS THE
29 OFFICIATING SERVICES PROVIDED BY AN OFFICIAL, AN UMPIRE, A REFEREE, OR A
30 JUDGE AT A HIGH SCHOOL SPORTING EVENT A HIGH SCHOOL SPORTS OFFICIAL
31 WHEN OVERSEEING A HIGH SCHOOL SPORT.

SENATE BILL 923 3
1 (5) “SIMILAR BOYS’ AND GIRLS’ HIGH SCHOOL SPORTS” MEANS HIGH
2 SCHOOL SPORTS THAT:
3 (I) OCCUR IN THE SAME SEASON;
4 (II) HAVE COMPARABLE RULES;
5 (III) HAVE A SIMILAR NUMBER OF HIGH SCHOOL SPORTS
6 OFFICIALS; AND
7 (IV) HAVE A SIMILAR TIME OF COMPETITION.
8 (B) A LOCAL SCHOOL SYSTEM SHALL ISSUE INVITATIONS FOR BIDS OR
9 REQUESTS FOR PROPOSALS FOR SIMILAR BOYS’ AND GIRLS’ HIGH SCHOOL SPORTS
10 OFFICIATING SERVICES SIMULTANEOUSLY.
11 (C) (1) A LOCAL SCHOOL SYSTEM MAY ISSUE AN INVITATION FOR BIDS OR
12 A REQUEST FOR PROPOSALS THAT REQUIRES A PROSPECTIVE BIDDER OR OFFEROR
13 TO INCLUDE IN A BID OR AN OFFER BOTH BOYS’ AND GIRLS’ HIGH SCHOOL SPORTS
14 OFFICIATING SERVICES.
15 (2) IF A LOCAL SCHOOL SYSTEM ISSUES SEPARATE INVITATIONS FOR
16 BIDS OR REQUESTS FOR PROPOSALS FOR BOYS’ AND GIRLS’ HIGH SCHOOL SPORTS
17 OFFICIATING SERVICES, THE LOCAL SCHOOL SYSTEM:
18 (I) MAY NOT SET SEPARATE DEADLINES FOR THE SUBMISSION
19 OF BIDS AND OFFERS FOR BOYS’ HIGH SCHOOL SPORTS OFFICIATING SERVICES AND
20 GIRLS’ HIGH SCHOOL SPORTS OFFICIATING SERVICES; AND
21 (II) MAY REQUIRE THAT PROSPECTIVE BIDDERS OR OFFERORS
22 PARTNER TO ENSURE THAT BIDS AND OFFERS FOR BOYS’ HIGH SCHOOL SPORTS
23 OFFICIATING SERVICES ARE ACCOMPANIED BY BIDS AND OFFERS FOR GIRLS’ HIGH
24 SCHOOL SPORTS OFFICIATING SERVICES.
25 (D) A LOCAL SCHOOL SYSTEM SHALL REJECT A BID OR PROPOSAL IF
26 ENTERING INTO A PROCUREMENT CONTRACT BASED ON THE BID OR PROPOSAL
27 WOULD RESULT, FOR SIMILAR BOYS’ AND GIRLS’ HIGH SCHOOL SPORTS, IN THE RATE
28 OF PAY OR ASSIGNING FEES RECEIVED BY INDIVIDUALS OFFICIATING GIRLS’ HIGH
29 SCHOOL SPORTS OR ASSIGNING GIRLS’ HIGH SCHOOL SPORTS OFFICIALS BEING
30 DIFFERENT FROM THE RATE OF PAY OR ASSIGNING FEES FOR INDIVIDUALS
31 OFFICIATING BOYS’ HIGH SCHOOL SPORTS OR ASSIGNING BOYS’ HIGH SCHOOL
32 SPORTS OFFICIALS.

4 SENATE BILL 923
1 (E) THIS SECTION MAY NOT BE CONSTRUED TO PROHIBIT THE PAYMENT OF
2 ASSIGNING FEES AS A BONUS THAT IS PAID OUTSIDE A PROCUREMENT CONTRACT.
3 (F) THE DEPARTMENT MAY DEVELOP GUIDELINES TO ASSIST A LOCAL
4 SCHOOL SYSTEM IN THE IMPLEMENTATION OF THE PROVISIONS OF THIS SECTION,
5 INCLUDING ADDITIONAL CRITERIA FOR DETERMINING WHICH HIGH SCHOOL
6 SPORTS QUALIFY AS SIMILAR BOYS’ AND GIRLS’ HIGH SCHOOL SPORTS.
7 (B) (1) ON OR BEFORE SEPTEMBER 1, 2025, THE DEPARTMENT, IN
8 CONSULTATION WITH THE MARYLAND PUBLIC SECONDARY SCHOOLS ATHLETIC
9 ASSOCIATION, SHALL DEVELOP A LIST OF SIMILAR HIGH SCHOOL SPORTS FOR BOYS
10 AND GIRLS.
11 (2) IN CATEGORIZING BOYS’ AND GIRLS’ SPORTS AS SIMILAR, THE
12 DEPARTMENT SHALL CONSIDER WHETHER EACH SPORT:
13 (I) OCCURS IN THE SAME SEASON;
14 (II) HAS COMPARABLE RULES;
15 (III) REQUIRES A SIMILAR NUMBER OF HIGH SCHOOL SPORTS
16 OFFICIALS;
17 (IV) REQUIRES SIMILAR HIGH SCHOOL SPORTS OFFICIATING
18 SERVICES; AND
19 (V) FEATURES COMPETITION OF COMPARABLE LENGTHS OF
20 TIME.
21 (3) THE DEPARTMENT, IN CONSULTATION WITH THE MARYLAND
22 PUBLIC SECONDARY SCHOOLS ATHLETIC ASSOCIATION, SHALL UPDATE THE LIST
23 EVERY 3 YEARS.
24 (C) (1) THIS SUBSECTION APPLIES TO A HIGH SCHOOL SPORTS OFFICIAL
25 WHO:
26 (I) IS AN EMPLOYEE OF THE LOCAL SCHOOL SYSTEM; OR
27 (II) IS EMPLOYED BY AN INDEPENDENT CONTRACTOR OR
28 OFFICIATING ASSOCIATION OR ORGANIZATION, WITH WHICH THE COUNTY BOARD
29 CONTRACTS.
30 (2) A COUNTY BOARD SHALL ENSURE THAT HIGH SCHOOL SPORTS
31 OFFICIALS RECEIVE THE SAME PAY IF THE OFFICIALS:

SENATE BILL 923 5
1 (I) ARE IN SIMILAR HIGH SCHOOL SPORTS OFFICIATING ROLES;
2 AND
3 (II) ARE PROVIDING OFFICIATING SERVICES FOR SPORTS
4 CATEGORIZED AS SIMILAR UNDER SUBSECTION (B) OF THIS SECTION.
5 (D) (1) A COUNTY BOARD SHALL REJECT A BID OR PROPOSAL FOR A
6 PROCUREMENT CONTRACT THAT WOULD RESULT IN DIFFERENT PAY OR FEES FOR
7 HIGH SCHOOL SPORTS OFFICIALS IN A SIMILAR HIGH SCHOOL SPORTS OFFICIATING
8 ROLE FOR SPORTS CATEGORIZED AS SIMILAR UNDER SUBSECTION (B) OF THIS
9 SECTION.
10 (2) WHEN SOLICITING INVITATIONS FOR A BID OR A REQUEST FOR A
11 PROPOSAL FOR HIGH SCHOOL SPORTS OFFICIATING SERVICES, A COUNTY BOARD
12 SHALL SOLICIT BIDS OR REQUESTS FOR A PROPOSAL FOR EACH SPORT WITHIN A
13 REASONABLE TIME OF THE SOLICITATION OF BIDS OR REQUESTS FOR PROPOSALS
14 FOR ALL SPORTS CATEGORIZED AS SIMILAR UNDER SUBSECTION (B) OF THIS
15 SECTION.
16 (E) (1) THIS SECTION MAY ONLY BE CONSTRUED TO REQUIRE PARITY
17 BETWEEN HIGH SCHOOL SPORTS OFFICIALS PERFORMING SIMILAR ROLES IN
18 SIMILAR SPORTS WITHIN A COUNTY AND MAY NOT BE CONSTRUED TO REQUIRE
19 PARITY IN HIGH SCHOOL SPORTS OFFICIALS BETWEEN COUNTIES.
20 (2) THIS SECTION MAY NOT BE CONSTRUED TO HAVE ANY EFFECT ON
21 THE GROUPING OF SPORTS TOGETHER FOR ANY PURPOSE OTHER THAN THE
22 PAYMENT OF HIGH SCHOOL SPORTS OFFICIALS OR FEES ASSIGNED TO CONTRACTS
23 FOR HIGH SCHOOL SPORTS OFFICIALS.
24 (3) THIS SECTION MAY NOT BE CONSTRUED TO PROHIBIT FEES
25 OUTSIDE OF A PROCUREMENT CONTRACT AS A BONUS TO HIGH SCHOOL SPORTS
26 OFFICIALS.
27 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That:
28 (a) A local school system that executed a procurement contract for high school
29 sports officiating services, as defined in § 4–147 of the Education Article, as enacted by
30 Section 1 of this Act, on or before July 1, 2025, may extend the term of the contract to align
31 the contract timelines for similar boys’ and girls’ high school sports.
32 (b) A local school system may not extend a contract under subsection (a) of this
33 section beyond July 1, 2029.

